    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Pieter Nanninck to Miklós Oláh (Leuven, 9 February 1539)</head>
                <floatingText>
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. Oláh has his sympathy in his grief for his lost
                            brother, and Nanninck wants to console him, but he cannot even ease his
                            own sadness. He is sending this elegy for his consolation. 2. He has
                            written him many times already what he thinks of <hi rend="italic"
                                >Athila</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Hungaria</hi>, he is not ashamed
                            of his opinion, unless it seems spiteful.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Reverendo domino Nicolao Olaho, thesaurario Albensi, archidiacono
                    Strigoniensi, serenissimi Ferdinandi Romanorum regis atc. ac Mariae reginae a
                    secretis et consiliis, Petrus Nannius salutem dicit.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Acerbissimos tuos luctus de amicissimo fratre<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.1">Máté Oláh died in 1536, see Oláh’s epitaphs on
                        his brother’s death: <hi rend="smallcap">Hegedüs</hi> 1906, 419–421; <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Fógel–Juhász</hi> 1934, 38–40; <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Neagu</hi> 2003, 342 –344. Oláh’s friends sent a heap of condolences,
                        elegies, and epitaphs from the Netherlands to lessen his grief, which
                        Nanninck published in print, see <hi rend="smallcap">Hegedüs</hi> 1906, 417;
                            <hi rend="smallcap">Tournoy</hi> 2006, 135–139. See the manuscripts:
                        ELTE EK H 46, fol. 31–43.</note> non lacrimis tantummodo, sed gravi
                    aegritudine animi prosequor, et ex laboribus adversae valetudinis, qua nunc
                    affligor, nihil tam triste sentio, quam cruciatus istius maeroris. Et ut
                    libenter studium consolandi prae me ferrem (tametsi tua sapientia et animi
                    fortitudo istiusmodi adminiculis non egeat), ita ipse vix <app xml:id="app.1">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.1"><choice>
                                <orig>inven<gap extent="1" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                                <supplied>inven<corr>io</corr></supplied>
                            </choice></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.1">invenio</rdg>
                    </app>, quo maestitiam meam commitigem. Quamobrem, ut in te consolando nonnihil
                    ipse acquiescerem, carmen hoc elegiacum super consolationes fraternae mortis,
                    quod ad te mitto, condidi, qualecumque ab animo ita misere afflicto exprimere
                    potui.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[Nunc utinam Pyliae…]<note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">See <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Tournoy</hi> 2006, 150–151.</note></p>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.4">[2.] De <app xml:id="app.2">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.2"><del corresp="Olahus">tua</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">tuo</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.2">tuo</rdg>
                    </app><hi rend="italic">Athila</hi> et Hungariae descriptione<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.3">I.e. <hi rend="italic">Hungaria</hi>.</note> quid sentiam,
                    iam saepius litteris meis testatus sum. Cuius me iudicii nunquam paenitebit,
                    nisi quod malignius videor et nimis parce rei laudatissimae laudes impertiisse.
                    Olim carmine testabimur, quantus mihi videare. Plura scriberem, sed doloribus
                    morbi huius ita excrucior, ut vix compos <app xml:id="app.3">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.3"><choice>
                                <orig>menti<gap extent="1" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                                <supplied>menti<corr>s</corr></supplied>
                            </choice></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.3">menti</rdg>
                    </app> sim.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Vale, Unicum <quote xml:id="quote.1">Praesidium Meum!</quote><note
                        type="quote" xml:id="note.quote.1">Cf. Hor. <hi rend="italic">Carm</hi>.
                        I,I,2.</note><note type="critic" xml:id="note.4">See Ep. 598. Cap.
                            3.<ref>olahus.tei.15371222_1</ref></note></p>
                <p xml:id="p.6"><placeName>Lovanii</placeName>, nona <app xml:id="app.4">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.4"><choice>
                                <orig>Februar<gap extent="1" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                                <supplied>Februar<corr>ii</corr></supplied>
                            </choice></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.4">Februarii</rdg>
                    </app> anno MDXXXIX.</p>
            </div>
